3.1.1 Getting to the Command Line

cli = command line line interface is a simple text input system 
for entering simple command to complicated scripts.

two ways to access the command line 

GUI based terminal 
virtual terminal

## GUI terminal is a program within the gui environment that emulates a terminal window 
## virtual terminal can be run at the same time as a GUI but requires the user to log in via the vertial terminal 
ordinary commands line tasks are 
starting programs 
parsing scripts
editing text files 

servers boot directly to the terminal.

